messages.subject: Re: Han vs. Luke and others
messages.msgSnippet: Well actually, I liked Hans Solo, too! Especially as the other episodes came out (part 5 & 6). I also liked Keith from the Partridge family. John Travolta at
messages.messageBody:
Well actually, I liked Hans Solo, too! Especially as the other episodes came out (part 5 & 6).
I also liked Keith from the Partridge family. John Travolta at one point. Love Arnold movies. Fonzie was cool.
There's probably others. My DH doesn't really look like any of them.

Karin


Pam wrote:

Ah, now see, I always wonder if we can tell things about each other by who
we had crushes on as young to middle teens.

Some of us (raises hand) liked the bad-good boys (Han Solo). Some of us (my
sister) liked the androgynous too-good boys (Luke).

I married a guy who looks like a bad boy. My sister married two Malibu Kens
in a row. <g>

Pam

----------
From: "Karin" <curtkar@...>
To: <AlwaysLearning@yahoogroups.com>
Subject: Re: [AlwaysLearning] Re: Anakin Skywalker's immaculate conception
Date: Fri, Dec 21, 2001, 10:32 AM


You're right about Anakin killing the emperor.
But for some reason, in my mind Luke is the hero.
Maybe it's the crush I had on Mark Hamill from so long ago. :-)

Karin



Earth Witch wrote:

Anakin was the chosen one, not Luke. As Vader, Anakin
kills the Emperor, and from that the balance comes.

Kitrina


--- Karin <curtkar@...> wrote:
> Of course! Chosen one to bring balance to the force.
> It's all coming back to me now. And in a way, Anakin
> was a vital piece of the puzzle to bring balance,
> being Luke's father, the real chosen one. (right?)
> I think it's time for another Star Wars marathon -
> it's been too long. :-D
>
> Karin

messages.msgSnippet: Han, Han. Hans makes me think of the horse that could do math ;-) He was my favorite, and my daughter likes him, too, although she prefers Harrison Ford  as
messages.messageBody:
Han, Han. Hans makes me think of the horse that could do math ;-) He was
my favorite, and my daughter likes him, too, although she prefers
Harrison Ford as Indiana Jones.

I liked Arnie, and Jean Claude van Damme, especially in Bloodsport - I
think his movies slid gradually downhill after that, but that was so bad
it was good. Also Gregory Harrison - must have a thing for the name
Harrison. And George was my Beatle..

Dar, just sorta mixed up
